Etymology 1[edit]

From lac +‎ -ō.

Verb[edit]

lactō (present infinitive lactāre, perfect active lactāvī, supine lactātum); first conjugation

  2. I contain or give milk, suckle.
  3. I suck milk from the breast.
  4. I am full of milk

Etymology 2[edit]

From laciō (“entice, allure”) +‎ -tō

Verb[edit]

lactō (present infinitive lactāre, perfect active lactāvī, supine lactātum); first conjugation

  2. I wheedle, flatter, deceive with flattery.
